'''''Professional Tour Golf''''' is a golf video game published by [[Strategic Simulations]] for the [[Apple II]] and [[Commodore 64]] in 1983.

==Gameplay==
''Professional Tour Golf'' is a game in which professional golf is simulated using the stats of professional golfers.<ref name="CGW14"/>

==Reception==
Roy Wagner reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "PTG is an excellent statistical simulation of golf both in play realism and in what can be learned for playing real golf with all the play options available, you will not get bored of this game very quickly."<ref name="CGW14">{{cite magazine |last=Wagner |first=Roy |title=Golf: Two Simulations |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=February 1984 |volume=1 |issue=14 |pages=25, 47}}</ref>

